I'm a newbie lvl 5 sorcerer. I didn't train any points until i hit 5....in which case, i think i put 3 shots into mind, and 2 into body so far. It's way too early for that to matter yet. Some say 24 mez is fine, other say get to 34 mez. But apparently the real discussion is whether to have the best nukes (210 base), or going 32+ in mind to get lvl 50 pets and dealing with 164 base nuke i think.  <P>My question is.....210 dd over 164. Is that THAT big of a difference? Is it a worthwhile difference over having a 50 pet? I'm only 5 as i said. I don't know the high end game on if 210pts a shot is worth it over 164.....and giving up lvl 50 pets. Are lvl 40+ pets great having? Or is there problems in pet control? They take too long to heal? They don't do enough damage? Once you find a lvl 41-50 pet, are they awesome to have? Can you go into another realm and find a humanoid pet and start sicking it on lvl 50 players? Or would it just get killed without your help?<P>I have no frame of mind of knowing the approx. hitpoints that players have at 50....So i have no basis on if giving up 210dd for a 164dd is worth the lvl 41-50 pets.<P>Can any high lvl sorcs give me insight on pets vs. dd damage on players? I would assume if you play to do RvR combat, then the max nuking is the way to go? Just because you don't want to always run around looking for a lvl 41-50 pet before you go kill people?<P><BR>Sorry for all the questions. I'm just your lil sorc brother, a little peon at lvl 5 just looking for some big brother wisdom ;D<P>Thanx for your time
