<HR size="1" color="#12350C">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
There are 3 common options :<P>44 Mind / 31 Body <BR>In this case it is better to use the highest Base Lifedrain DD ( third best DD ).  You will have the best AoE Mez in game and the best pet in game.<BR>34 Mind / 41 Body<BR>Here you will get the second best DD, the best pet and second best aoe mez.<BR>24 Mind / 48 Body<BR>With this one you will get the best DD, third best mez and second best pet.<P>It is not only the question of having the best nuke or having the best pet, it is also about having the best mez or not.<P>My preference goes too the 34 mind / 41 body, also important is that you only have to lvl till 46.5 to get the wanted spells, fot the other options you must go at least to 48 or 49, and I want that Telamon badly  <IMG SRC="wink.gif" border="0">.<P>In my limited experiance I feel that pets are a great addition, you can control them pretty well, and if it get's low on hitpoints you can get another one, at higher levels you can charm different types : humanoid, animal, insect and magical.  <P>I am sure it will help you in RVR , but when you loose your pet, it can be difficult to get a new one, because you must take the group and/or guild/alliance into account, they will probably not help you get a new pet so you must do this solo.  If you have a healer in the group then he or she can heal your pet.  <P>Also it does not steal RP's away from you, unlike in PVM, where your pet steals XP if it does damage, this also is no problem, set your pet to passive and it will never attack and never steal xp, but if the group does a bad pull you can quickly activate the pet so it might save your life, and/or that of the group.<P>Personally I love pets, so I am defenitly going for the 34 mind / 35 body spec.<P>All body/mind specs are viable so you can't really gimp yourself.<P>Amyway the best advice that I can give you is to lvl to 24 and spec 19 body / 14 mind and go play RVR in the BG's ( that is what I am going to do ), after that you can still decide what suits you most and you can go lvl to 30 and for example spec 22 body / 20 mind, and experiment with these specs in the BG's again.<P>After lvl 30 the decicion must be taken I think, but at that time you will probably know what suits you best.<P>--------------------<P>Cyberwiz lvl 42 Briton Ice Wizard<BR>Tuffir lvl 13 Briton Mind/Body Sorcerer<BR>Bors<BR>Proud Defenders Of Arcadia member
</FONT>
