<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Helvetica, sans-serif">
I agree with Bullseye.  34 in Mind seems a great price to pay for up-to level 50 pets.  And some pets have particular traits that make them desireable:  For instance, Elyll Windchasers have an AoE Nuke.  Emain Bloodletters take a lot of damage, and dish out a lot themselves.  Pets really do help out than if you didn't have them.<P>Bullseye said that you can go either Matter or Body.  Body has nukes and debuffs, plus a root.  Matter, as far as I know, currently only has a DoT.  DoTs are fine if they're your playstyle, but you'll have to expect that fights will take you time (since DoTs aren't usually stackable), so expect to be fighting the same mob for awhile.  Also, don't expect anything else in the Matter line for some time, while we have advocates trying to make Matter a bit more useful, we know how long it takes Mythic to do something (there are tons of bugs out there that could be fixed overnight, but aren't.  Like our DD still being energy?  Hint hint?), so don't expect things right around the corner in that department.
</FONT>
