/agree with Meekrobe.<P>I charmed one the other day and that is exactly what they did.  Casted confuse than ran around and tried to thump it with the stick.  It ran into a nest of carrion drakes and they killed the sorc rather quickly.  <P>One of the best hunting trips ever was with a level 49 tank, myself 47 sorc and an isolationist cleric.  We absolutely OWNED the 50-51 Cyreths(sp) on the opposite hill.  Got a piece of the formerly best cloth armor in Albion.  Was great.  The cleric did an outstanding job.<P>Ummm, be careful charming the Priestes of Purity in the Barrows.  Her older brother the Templar Knight takes offense to his sis being charmed and he will kill you very fast.  Plus, she is one of the auto-AF buffers and will not stop even when you take your own shiled down.<P>--------------------<P>Albundy NerfedAlot.  Gimped Sorcerer of Silent Redemption/Kay.  <BR>All-around bad player.
